---
title: 20 oz Rib-Eye Steaks with Chili-Tomato Jam, Scallion Mashed Potatoes, and Roasted Carrots
description: Why settle for a plain steak when you can make it juicier, bolder, and downright sensational with the addition of a well-chosen sauce? That’s exactly what’s happening here with the chili tomato jam that gets spooned onto this generous portion of rib-eye. It has tomato simmered down with chili flakes and vinegar until it’s a tour-de-force of tangy, savory, and spicy flavors. With some creamy mashed potatoes and honey-roasted carrots on the side, this steakhouse-style dinner turns into a real feast.
